Subject: [PATCH] ui: CSS variable theme bridge — native chrome to WebUI

Bridges Fennec CSS design tokens (src/ui/tokens/tokens.css) into the
native browser chrome (Views layer) so that the C++ UI and the React
WebUI share a single source of truth for colors, spacing, and animation
timings.

Implementation:
  1. FennecThemeService reads token values from the active theme
     (or user pref overrides written by the Mods system)
  2. It translates them to SkColor / gfx::Insets for the Views layer
  3. It also injects a <style> block into each fennec:// WebUI page
     with the current token values as CSS custom properties

This is what makes workspace chrome tints (--fnc-ws-tint) work: when
the user switches workspaces, WorkspaceManager calls
FennecThemeService::SetWorkspaceTint(), which both updates the Views
chrome background and re-injects --fnc-ws-tint into all open WebUI pages.

